 a nondescript morning, a cindery red-barred sunset sprawled on his canvas, and he was painting in the trees and various other details which, on the day before, advancing dusk had prevented him from completing. On a bench in a pine grove on the left a straight-backed girl was rapidly speaking (retaliation... bombs... cowards... oh, Phokus, if I were a man...) with nervous gestures of perplexity and dismay to a bluecapped student who sat with bent head and poked at scraps of paper, bus tickets, p